    Description
    AnimalDialog
    Abstract class implemented for the sake of inheritance (child classes: PreyDialog and PredatorDialog).
    Breeder
    Class created to implement the reproduction of animals.
    Converter
    Class used for converting values from one type to another, in cases where such conversions were not originally implemented in Java.
    Dialog
    Dialog Class implemented for the sake of inheritance.
    DistanceCalculator
    Class implemented as a means of calculating distance between two points
    Draw
    Class implemented as a means of visualizing paths
    LifeSourceDialog
    Class for dialog panel that shows when a LifeSource (WaterSource/Plant) is clicked on
    PlaceDialog
    Class used for visualization fo the dialog that shows up when a Hideout is clicked on, also the parent class for LifeSourceDialog
    PredatorDialog
    Dialog class used for visualization of the Predator class when it gets clicked on
    PreyDialog
    Class Representing PreyDialog, allows for visualization of fields present in Prey when an animal is clicked on.
